Description: Part of a jar-seal: of brown clay, bearing impressed inscriptions showing the repeated name of Aḥa. Only small areas of the inscriptions are now visible because of the poor state of preservation of this object.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl.XIV, 98; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.10, abb.27B; see also vol. II, 1094.
